Package fr.ign.artiscales.goal

Class ConsolidationDivision

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.ign.artiscales.goal.ConsolidationDivision
  • public class ConsolidationDivision
extends java.lang.Object
    Simulation following this goal merge together the contiguous marked parcels to create zones. The chosen parcel division process (OBB by default) is then applied on each created zone.
    Author:
    Maxime Colomb

        public static org.geotools.data.simple.SimpleFeatureCollection consolidationDivision​(org.geotools.data.simple.SimpleFeatureCollection parcels,
                                                                                     java.io.File roadFile,
                                                                                     java.io.File tmpFolder,
                                                                                     fr.ign.cogit.parameter.ProfileUrbanFabric profile)
                                                                              throws java.lang.Exception
        Method that merges the contiguous marked parcels into zones and then split those zones with a given parcel division algorithm (by default, the Oriented Bounding Box) overload of consolidationDivision(SimpleFeatureCollection, File, File, ProfileUrbanFabric) for no predefined harmony coeff and noise.
        Parameters:
        parcels - The parcels to be merged and cut. Must be marked with the SPLIT filed (see markParcelIntersectMUPOutput for example, with the method concerning MUP-City's output)
        roadFile - ShapeFile of the road segments. Can be null.
        tmpFolder - A temporary folder where will be saved intermediate results
        profile - ProfileUrbanFabric contains the parameters of the wanted urban scene
        Returns:
        the set of parcel with decomposition
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

        public static org.geotools.data.simple.SimpleFeatureCollection consolidationDivision​(org.geotools.data.simple.SimpleFeatureCollection parcels,
                                                                                     java.io.File roadFile,
                                                                                     java.io.File tmpFolder,

                                                                              throws java.lang.Exception
        Method that merges the contiguous marked parcels into zones and then split those zones with a given parcel division algorithm (by default, the Oriented Bounding Box). Without PolygonItersection used to operate a final selection
        Parameters:
        parcels - The parcels to be merged and cut. Must be marked with the SPLIT filed (see markParcelIntersectMUPOutput for example, with the method concerning MUP-City's output)
        tmpFolder - A temporary folder where will be saved intermediate results
        profile - ProfileUrbanFabric contains the parameters of the wanted urban scene
        harmonyCoeff - coefficient of minimal ration between length and width of the Oriented Bounding Box
        noise - level of perturbation
        Returns:
        the set of parcel with decomposition
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • consolidationDivision

        public static org.geotools.data.simple.SimpleFeatureCollection consolidationDivision​(org.geotools.data.simple.SimpleFeatureCollection parcels,
                                                                                     java.io.File roadFile,
                                                                                     java.io.File tmpFolder,
                                                                                     fr.ign.cogit.parameter.ProfileUrbanFabric profile,
                                                                                     java.io.File polygonIntersection,
                                                                                     double harmonyCoeff,
                                                                                     double noise)
                                                                              throws java.lang.Exception
        Method that merges the contiguous marked parcels into zones and then split those zones with a given parcel division algorithm (by default, the Oriented Bounding Box).
        Parameters:
        parcels - The parcels to be merged and cut. Must be marked with the SPLIT filed (see markParcelIntersectMUPOutput for example, with the method concerning MUP-City's output)
        roadFile - ShapeFile of the road segments. Can be null.
        tmpFolder - A temporary folder where will be saved intermediate results
        profile - ProfileUrbanFabric contains the parameters of the wanted urban scene
        polygonIntersection - Optional polygon layer that was used to process to the selection of parcels with their intersection. Used to keep only the intersecting simulated parcels.
        harmonyCoeff - coefficient of minimal ration between length and width of the Oriented Bounding Box
        noise - level of perturbation
        Returns:
        the set of parcel with decomposition
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
